According to the context, Redis is an open-source, in-memory database that can be used as a Key-Value (KV) store, and it's also referred to as a data structure store. It's primarily designed for fast access and retrieval of values by their keys.

As mentioned in the context, Redis was initially released under the name "Remote Directory Server" (Redis stands for Remote Dictionary Server). As for when Redis was released, according to the official Redis website, Redis 1.0 was released on March 10, 2005.
